canonical:
  title: 先涅庵
  author: 金宗直
  language: lzh
  text: 門掩藤蘿雲半扃雲根矗矗水泠泠高僧結夏還飛錫只有林閒猿鶴驚
  rtl: true
  vertical: true
lzh_formatted:
  title: 先涅庵
  author: 金宗直
  language: lzh
  text: 門掩藤蘿雲半扃。雲根矗矗水泠泠。高僧結夏還飛錫。只有林閒猿鶴驚。
korean:
  title: 선열암
  author: 김종직
  language: kor
  text: |-
    등라는 문을 가리고 구름은 반쯤 빗장을 질렀는데
    산은 뾰족뾰족하고 물은 졸졸 흐르도다
    고승은 여름 안거 마친 뒤 다시 멀리 떠나고
    다만 숲 속에는 원숭이와 학이 있어 놀라네
  url: https://db.itkc.or.kr/dir/item?itemId=BT#dir/node?dataId=ITKC_BT_1365A_1450_020_0490&viewSync=OT
  footnotes: []
english:
  title: The Hermitage of Prior Nirvana
  author: Kim Jong-jik
  language: eng
  text: |-
    Vines curtain the gate while clouds halfway bar the door,
    Mountain peaks pierce upward, waters murmur clear and cold.
    The great monk, his summer retreat complete, takes flight once more,
    Leaving only startled gibbons and cranes in the forest depths.
  footnotes:
    - Prior Nirvana (先涅) refers to a Buddhist predecessor or earlier enlightened master; the hermitage bears this name in veneration.
    - The 'summer retreat' (安居) refers to the Buddhist practice of Varsa, when monks gather during the rainy season for intensive practice and study.
    - The departure of the monk suggests the transient nature of even spiritual dwelling places, while the animals' alarm underscores the sudden disturbance of the hermitage's deep solitude.
